      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Philadelphia View</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Tom Goodman letter agrees with Bernard Holland's August 20th assessment of Riccardo Muti's abilities and attitudes (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Bernard Holland's assessment of Riccardo Muti's abilities and attitudes will resonate with audiences in Philadelphia. If anything, Mr. Holland understates two of the prickly maestro's highly undesirable qualities we Philadelphians suffered throughout his tenure here: his contempt for American audiences, whom he still views as interested only in entertainment, and his failure to ever record a single work that would be considered definitive in the Philadelphia Orchestra's discography.</p>
        <p>TOM GOODMAN  Wynnewood, Pa.</p>
      </block>
